text:
Absolutely flawless and spectacular hotel!!!! Cannot recommend them enough! We stayed here for 6 nights in September and it was above and beyond everything we could’ve imagined. 
Breakfast is amazing you get the choice of juice and tea, starter of bread and fruit, next course you chose a smoothie bowl or yogurt, then you chose a main the eggs Benedict and French toast is amazing and then finally if you have room you chose a traditional Indonesian meal... and they’re not small portions they filled us up through until afternoon tea. While in the subject afternoon tea is also amazing you look out onto the rice fields over a game of scrabble or cards provided and enjoy 2 savoury and 2 sweet dishes. 
The room was just breath taking we stayed in a jungle view villa with a private pool and it was honestly something out of a dream. The rooms were cleaned morning and night and they left extra touches such as a platter of fresh fruit every night and a bedtime story about the history of Bali. 
The staff are so attentive, polite and friendly they helped us organise many trips such as ATV driving and even contacted the company on our behalf to get us a special deal. 
The setting is amazing you walk past monkeys on your way in every day but they never enter the complex. We honestly cannot think of one negative thing to say we felt so sad to leave as so many amazing memories were made! It is in a prime location only a 10 minute walk to central Ubud but there is a FREE shuttle bus every 2 hours to the center of Ubud or they will organise an instant taxi at your request for a small payment. 
The hotel also offer drivers for half day or full day, we had a half day tour with our amazing driver WADER he was absolutely fantastic! He took us to 3 temples and the rice terrace and was so attentive from offering us cold drinks from a cooler in the boot to taking us to our exact desired destination (which a lot of the drivers you can get from other companies DO NOT do we asked for temples and they constantly took us to painting shops and wood carving shops where you get followed round and pressured into buying something. 
Thank you so very much to the amazing lovely staff you honestly made our time in Ubud so much more special and we will not hesitate to come back if we visit Bali again. 
Katie and Ollie
title: A hotel of dreams! Perfect stay!

A new hotel in Ubud - walking distance to shops and restaurants. Because of its location being next to the Monkey Forest, we could see monkeys in the forest surrounding the hotel property in the morning, and once we had a monkey visiting us on our terrace which was extremely entertaining. 
Hotel staff are extremely nice and friendly, always ready to help you. Nevertheless, we had a perfectly satisfying experience overall. The on-site restaurant serves excellent food, which isn't more expensive than other good restaurants in town. Their burger was so juicy and very delicious! Breakfast is a la carte, so everything is made fresh for you and lots of very nice options to choose from. 
Because of its location surrounded by nature, we did find some insects (and a gecko) occasionally in our villa. But even as a person who hates insects, it was't a big deal for me after all  because everything else about the hotel was just excellent. I appreciated the plug-in mosquito repellent which was provided in the villa which worked well.
We had a villa with a plunge pool overlooking the forest - which was really nice and highly recommended.

text:
Extremely fortunate to have just spent 5 nights at this incredible hotel over new year. 

I struggle to believe there is a better place in the whole of Ubud, as Tejaprana Bisma has it all.

Location is absolutely perfect; you have that 'away from it all' feeling, with glorious views from the main pool overlooking the valley and rice fields in the distance.
Yet you have the huge benefit of being able to wander into the centre of Ubud in about 15 minutes, where there are plenty of shops and restaurants. (there are also plenty of places to eat and drink within a few minutes from the hotel)
You're also only 5 minutes round the corner from Monkey Forest. 
It really is the best of both worlds here.

Within the hotel, you have the fantastic villas, all complete with a private plunge pool.
I had the valley view villa and it was perfect. 
Really liked the outdoor space and even if it rained, you could still sit outside on the sheltered daybed.
The pool was inviting and refreshing. 

The main had that spectacular view and was a great option if you wanted to get a proper swim in.

The food was lovely; breakfast delicious with plenty of options and also had a couple of evening meals there that were also lovely. 

Another big highlight of the hotel was the staff and service; all incredibly friendly and helpful, from reception through to housekeeping and restaurant. 
They all seemed genuinely happy in their work and were always smiling and offering a warm greeting.

Didn't use the spa so can't comment on that.

The only slight drawbacks were the spotty WiFi (1st world problems indeed), which sometimes cut out for quite long periods, and the price of things like cocktails within the hotel bar did seem a little steep. However, it is a 5* hotel so nothing too out of the ordinary there.

I think it's only a matter of time before Tejaprana Bisma is ranked No1 on here, and it will be extremely well deserved when it gets to the top of the tree.
I will be back and would urge anyone else thinking of stopping in Ubud (which is absolutely lovely) to get booked in here, you won't regret it.

text:

title: Impeccable service

text: Our tour guide and driver, Made Sudarmayasa, made our stay extra special. He was very knowledgeable, flexible, courteous and funny. He showed us around almost every day for a week. We also really enjoyed our private swimming pool and outdoor bathtub. The entire staff was very friendly and helpful.  Short walk to monkey forest, too. Highly recommend!
title: Excellent staff and private swimming pool!!

text:
The resort is fantastic. The villa room is clean and comfortable. The amenities are aplenty. The resort is quiet and provides a tranquil experience to us.

We love the infinity pool near the restaurant. It has a wonderful view of the forest and the cute animals, as well as a beautiful sunset view. The outdoor pool is always well maintained.

The staff are welcoming and warm to all customers. They always greet you with a smile and make you feel at home.

A special shoutout to the staff Ita who welcomed us warmly at the hotel, Ariani who served our meals at Kalyana restaurant, Wedi who kindly drove us to the airport at such a short notice, not to mention the housekeepers who kept our room so tidy everyday. Matur Suksma!
title: Fantastic Stay, Awesome Staff

text: Beautiful location and lovely staff that will do all they can to accommodate requests and ensure a relaxing experience. Though not close to central Ubud the resort is within easy walking distance to Monkey Forest Road which has ample restaurants for food, cocktails, and live music. The rooms are comfortable with an extra large bed, and our terrace view villa infinity pool had an amazing view. We were able to relax in the pool while watching the Macaques, birds, and butterflies. Daily visits from the Macaques to our terrace was an enjoyable bonus so we felt no need to visit the Monkey Forest. Would return to this resort and wish we had more time here.
title: A lovely relaxing short break holiday.

text:
Staff and hotel was amazing 
I loved my room with its private pool massive bathroom outdoor bath; but the Spa treatments and staff were fantastic, and drivers and reception staff were so good to us 
I will recommend and I will be back soon
Again !!
title: AMAZING Grace

text:
Beautiful stay, really nice hotel. Staff was friendly, attentive and professional at all times, nothing was too much for them. Will definitely stay here again. Thanks team for making our stay so special. 
The Hotel is also located ner to Beautiful shops and cafe.
title: Wonderful stay

text:
From the moment we arrived the service and kindness and beautiful smiles from the staff was outstanding!
Our room was beautiful and clean and tidied each day. The splash pool was fantastic as we could jump in and it was private and secluded.
Breakfast was lovely especially the fruit and the service and politeness from staff was fabulous.
It was a short walk into town along Bisma or monkey Forrest road and many fabulous restaurants. Yoga classes are everywhere and silver shops.
Ubud is a great place to relax and unwind and I would certainly recommend Tejaprana to anyone :)
title: Excellent relaxing peaceful break for 2!

text: Beautiful room with private infinity plunge pool with views into the valley, jungle and beyond. Super helpful and friendly staff from FO, housekeeping, and restaurant. Amazing facility, great location and 5 minutes walk to Monkey forest, restaurants etc. we definitely will be back. Thank you so much Tejaprana Bisma
title: Paradise in the valley

text:
One of the best experiences. Every detail was taken care of, I can't name one as all of them were at their very best in making you feel comfortable. We had a few out-of-the-box requirements and they made it possible. I can't recommend it enough.

Thanks to the whole team and a big shout-out, you all deserve a big appreciation.
title: One of the best experiences.

text: The vila was beatiful, the bed comfy and the staff amazing. We had a great time and loved our stay. The breakfast was delicious and we were pleasently surprised to get a cappuccino with breakfast. athe only downer was the stairs.
title: Beautiful villa

text: We had a wonderful stay at this truly beautiful hotel.  The Villa was extremely comfortable, immaculately clean, with a beautiful plunge pool overlooking a tropical garden view. The breakfasts were brilliant served on the terrace near the infinity pool. All staff were exceptionally friendly, polite and professional. Probably the best hotel we have ever stayed in (and we have stayed in many around the world). We throughly enjoyed our 4 night stay in Ubud, due in no small part to our stay at the Tejaprana. We would definitely stay here again and highly recommend to anyone. Definitely a 5 star experience.
title: Absolutely first class

text:
We had an amazing experience at the Tejaprama Bisma. The hotel is locate at the end of central Jalan Bisma, hidden away amongst the trees, rice paddies and fields. This makes it very tranquil whilst still in the middle of central Ubud. A highlight of the experience was the wonderful staff. They always happy to help and deliver excellent service, food and drinks. The a la carte breakfast was delicious with many options to choose from. Although the venue is set over multiple levels overlooking the valley where you can see a beautiful sunset from the pool or bar, it is still wheelchair/ disability accessible. 

Pros: 
Great location
Perfect service 
Brilliant food
Stunning rooms 
Friendly staff 

Cons:
Too much nature!!!
title: Excellent! Wowee!

text: Really enjoyed our stay, and would have loved to stay longer. The villa had an infinity pool and also a large tub outside with recliners by the pool and also a gazebo with table and chairs. The valley views were lovely. The villa itself was very spacious as well. A large king bed that was comfy. The furnishings were all quality. A pod coffee machine and also 4 bottles of water was much appreciated each day. All meals we had were very good. All staff were very pleasant and nothing was too much trouble. I would definitely recommend and would love to return for longer next time.☺️
title: A wonderful stay.

text: Amazing place to stay. Close to town yet you feel like you are in the countryside. Beautiful room and exquisite restaurant. The best part were the staff - they were so friendly, welcoming and professional.
title: Slice of Heaven

text: This is my favourite hotel ever. We stayed in a beautiful villa with private pool, bordering straight onto the forest. Lovely staff, wonderful spa/massages, and very good restaurant. Our driver Made was such a good guide, with excellent English, and we think of him as a friend. We will be back, en masse
title: So good!

text: We stayed here for the first week of our Bali holiday and we were not disappointed, we had a garden villia which was amazing. This is such a well thought out respond every Villa is secluded with no one looking in to any part so very private. We even had a monkey jump in to our villa and take a swig of my beer which was amazing.  The staff and service are second to none fabulous not once did we have to tell any staff member our name or room number. This resort borders the monkey sanctuary so very handy for access. If you can’t relax here you honestly don’t have a chance of relaxing anywhere. The only addition I would make to the rooms would be a mosquito net, but the staff do spray the room at turndown and have plug ins so it’s a minor complaint and not enough to put you off staying here. Tejaprana thank you for a fantastic week.
title: A sanctuary of calm and relaxation

text: The staff was very friendly. The room, pool, and the restaurant/bar were amazing! We loved the signature cocktails so much! We had a luxury stay here and will definitely recommend it to all the travelers.
title: Luxury stay

text: We spent 4 wonderful nights here in a garden view villa, and from the moment we were picked up in the Tejaprana vehicle by our driver Awan, and transported from Nusa Dua to Ubud,  we felt welcomed. The staff are world class here, from remembering each guest by name, to the nightly mosquito coil lighting service, to the warm greetings from the garden and maintenance staff, this is pure excellence. The Spa is extremely professional and luxurious, the breakfast delicious, and the dinner we had was also lovely. We didn't want to leave. Well done Tejaprana, we will be back!
title: Five star excellence in paradise

text: Well, actually i went here for a meeting but i decided to stay here and it was perfect! The rooms are clean, the food is really good and, it has a private pool! This is the nicest hotel i've ever visited.
title: The best hotel i've ever been!

text: We visited from the United States, this is our 2nd time to Bali. Tejaprana Bisma is in the ideal location to walk to downtown Ubud or use as a home base with your car or scooter, when you're on the property it feels like you're in a mixture of a jungle and a rice patty yet far removed from any urban setting. Great restaraunts nearby. We rented the 2 bedroom pool villa and during our stay we arranged through Tejaprana Bisma to have someone from the hotel's staff to watch after our kids. They did so from 10-3 each day for 4 days for a very reasonable rate and did cooking classes, kite making, a local village visit, monkey forest, bali zoo...so the kids had an incredible time as did us adults! When we got home, the kids said the best part of the trip was the time they spent with Yoga (their guide). We hope to come back!!
title: No better place to stay in Ubud!

text:
We were so looking forward to returning to Ubud after the Covid lockdown and our expectations were exceeded with our stay at the Tejaprana Bisma.  The hotel is only a few years old and is absolutely beautiful. We stayed in a one bedroom Sacred Valley view pool villa and the attention to detail in the design and fittings such as the little thatched ceiling above the outdoor bath and the amazing hanging copper 
Iight fittings to name a few really point to why this hotel is a one-of-a-kind. We had a few visits from the monkeys which we loved, but if this is not your thing the staff are more than happy to gently address this.  And speaking of the staff- they were truly outstanding- friendly and down to earth.  The Tejaprana is owned designed and built by a Balinese architect which you really feel in the overall experience of the resort itself and the very special people who work there.

text: From the moment we arrived to the moment we departed, the staff were amazing.  Our room was geneorus and clean with a lovely private pool looking out to farm area with a lovely local cow. text:

title: Lovely Bali villas in a quiet but very convenient location

text:
I felt like I arrived in Paradise.

title: Welcome to Paradise!

text: Everything about the hotel, from reception, to the villa, the food, and our general experience was phenomenal. There is nothing wrong about the hotel, period. It’s photos on Booking and TripAdvisor don’t give it justice.
title: Best hotel I have been visited  in Ubud

text:
Wow, where to even begin with the (much-deserved) accolades for this property? My second trip to Ubud, Bali was nothing short of magical in this accommodation, which offers precisely the attributes I seek when traveling: serenity, service, and surreal scenery. Amazingly, while the villas are located well within walking distance of Ubud, they are set just far enough back for guests to truly enjoy the quiet and amazing views of rice terraces while enjoying the included breakfast. Room service was also fantastic, with remarkably fresh, high quality meals at extremely reasonable prices; we stayed four nights and ordered room service at least three different times: It was that good, as well as that efficient. Special shout out to Ariani, who went out of her way to make our stay wonderful, though every single staff member was truly remarkable in the extent to which they would go out of their way to help you.

We also used the spa services twice, which were extremely well priced; the massages were excellent and made the retreat back to the villa overlooking the rice terraces all the more relaxing. Speaking of the villa, the outdoor bathtub for soaking is especially divine, and the covering enables one to soak and enjoy the nature even when it begins to rain.

As far as touring Ubud and several other sites within two hours' driving distance, the services of Angga are very strongly recommended: He is remarkably accommodating, friendly, and more than willing to assist tourists with site seeing and excellent eating! We had a fantastic day trip up to Bratan Lake/Beratan Temple, as well as Jatiluwih Rice Terraces, the largest rice terraces in Bali, which also received UNESCO distinction in 2012, as we learned from Angga. Having a private driver in a very comfortable, tinted car at an extremely reasonable price was a fantastic additional benefit.

Would absolutely stay here again whenever in Ubud, and it is absolutely recommended without reservation.
title: Amazing Ambiance and Exceptional Service

text: Excellent property. Staff at every level were exceptional. Wished we had more time to enjoy the place. It’s in Ubud, right in the middle of the island, making it a convenient location to visit the north, east, west and south of the island. Definitely 5 star. A must stay!

text: This trip was our first time in Bali. We stayed in two 4-star accomodations and this one is our 5 star one! The masseuses were so professional; both myself and my wife tried their signature massage and facial. Prices of the restaurant and spa was very reasonable.
title: luxury experience with friendly staff

text:
Very friendly and helpful staff. Great location with walking distance to monkey forest (monkeys come and visit your pool area sometimes, they stay out of the pool thought) and Ubud centre. The room is very nice and clean. Excellent breakfast.
Recommended.
title: Ubud 22

text: I've been to Ubud once before but this trip was the best and a lot of that is because of Tejaprana. Wonderful room with our own pool and felt like a piece of heaven. Awesome service from Juan who helped us with tips and a SIM card. Thank you!
title: Best experience in Ubud so far

text: Wow! From the calm and relaxed drive up to Ubud to the welcome drink to the gorgeous suite with private pool! To the infinity edge main pool, to the great food and service... to the Friday night Salsa party to the efficient, well-trained staff... just WOW! Easy walk to town but really, you could almost just chill at the resort and on Jalan Bisma for a week and not get bored! Do yourself a massive favour and stay here.
title: Relaxing and Luxurious! What more could you wish for?

text:
We stayed in the jungle view villa for 3 nights and had a beautiful experience. The views were breathtaking and extended for horizons. The rooms were clean and architecture was carefully curated. 

The hotel breakfast was delicious, especially the coffee. 

The spa massage was a high light. 

Thank you for the hospitality.

The location was ideal - far enough out to be quiet and peaceful, but within walking distance of bars and restaurants. Would 100% recommend!
title: Wonderful stay

text:
What an amazing hotel!
Firstly the staff here are phenomenal! Not only did they remember orders and my name but I also have an allergy. Staff were so clear with following up with my allergy and making it safe! The rooms were gorgeous with monkeys around and calm nature. All modern amenities I love the outdoor bath!

Thanks for a great stay

text: The most amazing place with beautiful surroundings and very polite and friendly staff. They always ensure their guests are having a good time and don't miss anything. Me and my friend were picked up at the airport by Babak Angga from Tejaprana Bisma. We had a safe and nice trip to the hotel. A few days after we booked him as our driver for a day trip. He was the best driver and guide that we could imagine. We booked him as a driver, but he also acted like a guide. He told us a lot about the temple and the rice terrace that we saw, about history and culture. Since we regretted some of the sights we had planned, Babak Angga quickly suggested some nice attractions instead. Tejaprana Bisma and Babak Angga have our warmest recommendations. Matur suksma Tejaprana Bisma and Babak Angga 🙏🍀
title: Best vacation ever at Tejaprana Bisma with Babak Angga as our driver and guide

text: Our stay at the Tejaprana Bisma was PERFECT. Our villa was thoughtfully decorated for our honeymoon and the staff was incredible and so kind. The food at the restaurant was also the best we had in Ubud! My husband’s first and only (so far) spa experience was also a huge success thanks to the pampering of the Tejaprana Bisma masseuses. We already miss it and would not hesitate to stay here again. We will be recommending this hotel to all our friends journeying to Bali soon for their honeymoons!
title: Perfect honeymoon

text:
Absolutely incredible stay here. We were on the early side of tourism restarting once VOAs reopened a few weeks ago, and got a fantastic deal here. Room was spacious, shower fantastic, two sets of closets (and robes and slippers). The private pool was a luxury. We would sit on the shallow side, reviewing the day and enjoying being cooler. 

The staff was amazing, too! Incredibly polite and some of the most helpful and friendly anywhere. The special touches were amazing! Two umbrellas just outside our door, nightly turndown service, mosquito coils (!!) lit at dusk and put under our outdoor sofa so we could continue taking advantage of the outdoor space.

I had read online that some people were concerned about the monkeys. Breakfast has a monkey security guard now (I'm not kidding) and we never had a monkey interfere with breakfast. We encountered some just outside the resort, but waited for the group of them to cross the street and it was fine.

The resort is on the edge of town, and it was nice to escape the crowds of central Ubud. We had no issues walking 10 minutes to dinner or 20 minutes to the center.

Our only regret was leaving. 10/10 would recommend.
title: Phenomenal experience

text:
On our way from North Bali to the South we stayed unfortunately (!!) only one night @ this outstanding hotel.
We had a pool villa with perfect and beautiful forest view. 
The breakfast was tasty and the restaurant area beautiful. All the staff were extremly helpful and friendly. The only thing we missed was an umbrella @ the pool terrace of our villa. Steadily lying in the sun is not that healthy. So I already recommended this to the front desk.
Anyway we‘ll definitly come back soon!
Terima kasih banyak!!
title: Perfect staying @ a perfect location served by perfect staff!

text: We are traveling more than two weeks in Bali. We stayed in several different 5 stars hotels. But we were still amazed by this one. Everyone we came across in the hotel were super nice. It's the most worthit hotel we've stayed in. The manager Yuli was very professional, she helped us solved our problem with the traffic polices. They came to us just right after I called which I didn't expect. During our stay, we used the hotel car rental service. We had a nice trip with Veda who drove us around. He was a good driver and a very nice fun person to have conversations with. We felt like we made a friend in our trip. Thanks to him we had some knowledges of local culture now. Usually I would consider staying in hotels would lose connection with the local people. This hotel changed my mind. We had a very private villa room with wonderful jungle view next to the monkey forrest. The breakfast there was amazing too. We ended up staying longer. If you ever have a chance to come to Ubud, you must stay in this hotel. I am sure they will not let you down. 100% recommended!
title: exceptional services

text:

Great job, Tejaprana bisma
title: Perfect getaway

text:

title: Had great time in Valley View villa

text: It was a short meeting visit in Tejaprana Bisma in Ubud, I must say that they are doing a great Job in this pandemic; maintaining an Amazing product which itself is a great thing. text:
I was in a dire need of a good secluded escape after facing months of staying home due to the pandemic. I was emotionally burnout and lethargic with my work, so I then decided to book a 3 nights stay at Tejaprana Bisma.

I've been eyeing this hotel for quite some time actually. Who would've known, I came at the most unfortunate time, where most people refrained from taking holiday just to be safe and healthy. For the record, if the pandemic isn't over by the time you read this, I endorsed you to stay at home. 

When talking about luxury in hospitality industry, usually it rhymes with big names of certain hotel chains. Often depicted for having a serene atmosohere, gorgeous design, scenic pool, and top notch personalized service. I am hapoy to say that you'll find those here at Tejaprana Bisma. 

Let's get into details....

LOCATION
Tejaprana Bisma located at the end of Bisma Street.
To get to Bisma Street, you'll need to pass Monkey Forest Rd, take the left turn onto Ubud Raya St. Then take a left turn onto a bit steep street. The road to Tejaprana Bisma a bit rocky and uneven width. But fits for two cars. Along the Bisma St, you'll find various shops, restaurants and cafe. Unfortunately, when I stayed here, most of them were closed. By the time you reached the end of the street, turn right, look for Tejaprana Bisma signage. I don't think, you'll miss this. Monkey Forest Rd can be reached within minutes from Tejaprana Bisma. There's a shortcut by pass, around 200 metres from the property. Cars can't pass this shortcut, but motorcycles can.
In conclusion: Tejaprana Bisma is well hidden. You'll get a nice and calm atmosphere yet close enough to find some bustling atmosphere.

ROOM/VILLA
It's big! You'll find an oversize King bed with 4 fluffy pillows, a wooden bench, a dining table, and a 43 inch TV.
A walk in wardrobe, toilet, His and Her sinks, outdoor bathtub, rain shower and ...jet bidet shower with hose on its toilet (I don't like the one with built-in bidet, hard to control and sometimes the stream not too strong enough to clean 😜)
Each room is equipped with a plunge pool with 1.4 metre / 4.5 ft depth. 
There are several types of Villas: Villa with garden view (your POV will be blocked by a wall, since it is facing to the street), Villa with rice paddy field view (overlook to a vast rice paddy field), Villa with terrace view (overlook to other villa roof) and the last is Villa with valley view (overlook to a gorge and in distant rice paddy field across the gorge).
I chose Villa with valley view. There are 6 villas of this type. It offers more secluded privacy compared to others. Since it offers more privacy, it is located the furthest from lobby. But, worry not. Tejaprana Bisma landscape is well designed. So a bit of stroll to the Villa with valley view will be enjoyable. Although, for those who came with elderly and small children, this hotel might not be suitable. There are stairs everywhere. So, be careful.

SERVICE
For me, an excellent customer service, makes all the difference. And I have to say, Tejaprana Bisma crews exceeds my expectations. From a printed personal note from resort manager welcoming you  by the time you entered your villa to your presence being acknowledged by every staff members. By acknowledged, I mean, they know your name and greet you by your name. Not many hotel did this small act of gesture. Every staffs were very courteous yet not pretentious. There's a difference between forced attention / care and genuinity. Every staff seemed willing to go the distance to meet their guest's need.

I would like to thank you to Tejaprana Bisma staffs for making my stay worthwhile. I'm feeling refreshed after staying here. I rarely go back to the same hotel that I went to. But, I will surely be back soon.

text:
This review might sound nitpicky but when you are comparing with all the other amazing accommodation in Bali, every part counts, especially if you are marketing a place as a luxury 5 star accommodation & truly wish to stand out. 
PROS
The villas themselves are beautiful, though the pool is small.
Breakfast and food was another plus - the quality of food is excellent and everything we tried was truly delicious. 
This place is very economical compared to other accommodation
Weda was an excellent guide and driver - he drove us on a half day trip to a number of locations & was so pleasant, conscientious and helpful.

CONS
Where I think they could improve is the attention to detail in their service which may come down to better training for staff. 
Examples:
- I had to call then finally visit the reception twice to arrange transport to a restaurant (though the girl at the desk , apologies I don't remember her name) appeared very nice and said she would arrange everything she did not & failed to make arrangement or hand it over to the next staff (clearly because the next person had no idea what I was talking about)
- Also called multiple times for an iron - again the front staff said they would send one to the room when ready, when I called to check again clearly they had forgotten to do so & also failed to hand over to the next person on shift to do
- Called multiple times about our laundry - had been given at 1000 one morning & should have been ready by the next afternoon at the latest. Well, it was 1am and we still hadnt received the laundry despite checking out the next morning and having called reception TWICE about it, each receiving the same generic spiel.
- Asking about particular ingredients at breakfast & the server stated "I will check with the chef and get back to you" - well we never saw him again & he neatly avoided us.

Other dislikes - 
- Mosquitos - lots of mosquitos in the room despite my husband and I being extremely strict about leaving the doors closed at all times. This meant we did not sleep particularly well. I am not sure how they come in but I note they leave the front door wide open while they clean the rooms. I also noted that the mosquito repellant was unplugged some nights. I have stayed in other Bali accommodation and have not had problems with mosquitos. Perhaps you could at least put a canopy on the bed?
- THe wardrobe hanging storage is not adequate - very narrow and the hangers are permanently attached to the rod meaning its almost impossible to hang your clothes up (and I have very small hands)

So all in all - the stay was nice but since there were a number of minor details that could have been improved I wouldn't stay here again & and I wouldnt give it 5 stars. 
In short, there is room for improvement especially in the service department - 
the main thing being that whilst anyone can smile and nod and be "nice" and "friendly", it is important to actually deliver substance. Don't be all talk and no action!

text:
We stayed here for 2 nights in November. On arrival, we were blown away with the hotel- absolutely beautiful! Loved all the greenery and flowers, the fish ponds, the rooms are beautiful, having your own infinity pool is a definite plus, and absolutely loved the out door stone bath and the views over the rice fields and jungle. 
We had the floating breakfast one morning which was a bit of a gimmick but fun all the same, no compromise on flavours or presentation. Breakfast at the main restaurant was also delicious, and not over crowded. 
The main area that could be improved here is the cleanliness. It’s not dirty, however it lacks attention to detail. For example the mirrors are clearly not cleaned properly, when you shower you can see all the previous soap/water marks on the mirrors. 
After we had finished our floating breakfast we naturally left the plates in the garden so as not to attract bugs inside our room. However when we returned from our outing, the room had been cleaned, but the plates had not been taken away? We phoned reception and they sorted it out straight away, just slightly surprising considering those cleaning the room would have seen the plates, but did not remove them. 
When we arrived i stepped on a Small shard of glass.  Only tiny but could have been prevented all the same. 
The pillowcases did have a stain on them, while I am sure they were clean, it is simply unsightly, and leads you to question the cleanliness off other areas. 
There were also hundreds of ants in the room, almost all dead, crowded by the door. Not quite sure what phenomenon was going on! I took it upon myself to try and clear them up and did manage to get rid of most of them, however when the room was
Cleaned there appeared to be no effort to clear up the remaining ants? This could have been that they were cleared up and then more subsequently came and died, it’s difficult to know. This did lead to the unfortunate event of finding the odd ant on the bed or sofa. While I appreciate this is a resort in a countryside location, and wildlife is inevitable, it would be nice to feel as though every effort is taken to prevent this. The hotel did provide a mosquito repellant plug-in which was nice, but nothing for the ants (I’m not sure if such a thing exists?). 
Over all we did not let this spoilt our stay, and still had a very pleasant stay, the staff could not do enough for us, just a few minor things that could make this place even better.

title: Beautiful new resort

text:
If you're like me, you've clicked through page after page of beautiful hotel listings in Bali. You've read reviews wondering whether you could trust the authors opinion, done research on the area, looked at blog posts by travel influencers, and carefully whittled down your options for where to stay on your big trip. 

Skip that whole process. Book at the Tejaprana Bisma. 

The rooms are beautifully appointed, extremely spacious and clean, and are a perfect oasis from the hustle and bustle of Ubud. It's centrally located making for an easy walk to most anywhere you'd want to go in town. Each room has some sort of plunge pool which we took full advantage of after long days of sightseeing. If you can, splurge on the Valley View room which gives you an unobstructed view of lush jungle while you relax in/near the water. 

Breakfast was excellent, and I'm very much a discerning breakfast person. I disagree with other reviews that said the food was bad. There was a wide variety, and they were happy to bring you as much or as little food as you wanted. They also offer complimentary afternoon tea/coffee with a rotating assortment of snacks. The service was also exceptional, their team did everything they could to make us feel welcome and comfortable. Ariani was our server at breakfast and tea most days, and offered recommendations in town, and taught us a few phrases in Balinese.

Bottom line, while there are certainly less expensive hotels in Bali, I still think this hotel is a fantastic value for your money if it's within your price range. The amenities offered compared to the price point seemed to exceed anything competitor hotels offered. It felt like we were staying in a hotel straight out of an architecture magazine.

I would absolutely stay here again and would tell my friends to do so too if they were coming to the island. 

p.s. There is another hotel under construction next door, but they look to be nearing completion, and honestly we never noticed/had a problem with noise level.
title: Stop your search. Get a room here.

title: Fantastic! Didn’t want to leave

text:
Tejaprana Bisma is truly top notch. My husband and I stayed for four nights at the start of our honeymoon in Bali and it was the best one we stayed at compared to the other two we stayed in Jimbaran and Nusa Dua for the rest of our trip. Special thanks to Weda, Dewa, and Octa who were helpful to us both before and during our stay.

Octa was helpful before our arrival, answering all our questions before our stay. Our check-in was seamless as we were greeted by Dewa who spoke perfect English and explained all about the property on our arrival. Dewa also helped us book our transport and tickets to the Bali Safari which made our visit there very smooth and convenient. 

The property also provides a free shuttle service to Ubud Palace every hour but you need to “book” (you just need to tell them at front desk a couple of mins before as they like to prepare the car so that it’s nice and cool when you get in - they’re just super attentive and caring). The first time on the shuttle we had Weda and we requested for him to be our driver since (Trip to and fro Safari as well as taking us to next destination in Jimbaran). Weda speaks very good English, is friendly and very helpful. On the longer journeys he’d prepare cold drinks for us after each stop and during the journey he’d tell us about local culture (rather than hard selling any places which we are always fearful of). By the way my husband is now obsessed with Bali United - a football team that Weda supports as he was telling us about a football match that night, making us feel like we’re one of the locals! It is always a bonus to be able to make new friends whilst you travel. 

The room we stayed in was spacious with its own private  plunge pool, indoor shower and an outdoor bath. The outdoor area is pure bliss. Tejaprana Bisma is only opened earlier in 2019 so everything was still pretty new. The only downside was that our bedroom was always filled with mosquitoes (it’s just an Ubud thing I think) and despite the team of staff doing all they can with the situation, we were still being disturbed by the mosquitos during our sleep. If management is reading, I recommend adding mosquito nets around the bed then Tejaprana Bisma will truly be PERFECT. Read on to find out the other good things it has to offer. 

Breakfast was included throughout our stay. It is a fully serviced, made to order breakfast. The food is absolutely superb and we truly have to compliment the chef, kitchen staff, and restaurant staff. What a professional team of people! See the photos attached and you will know what I mean. The waiters managed to remember my preference for tea by the second day we went for breakfast. Such heartwarming service - made you feel at home! The view of the rice terrace whilst having breakfast was also a plus! My husband is telling me to not bore you all with how much I loved the breakfast as I had better let you find out yourself to fully enjoy the experience!

Tejaprana Bisma also offers a daily complimentary afternoon tea in their lounge. It’s a shame that we only had the chance to have it once (we went out a lot). The food was again top notch and the view from the lounge was very relaxing. 

Oh and one more plus - they use exquisite crockery at their restaurant and lounge. All by Kevala Ceramics - look it up and you’ll know what I mean. The whole experience was just amazing - running out of amazing adjectives here. 

Enough of words for now - I should let the photos speak for itself. Thank you to the whole team at Tejaprana Bisma for making our stay so awesome and memorable!

text:
There are honestly no faults I could think of for this hotel. The location is perfect, right by the monkey forest and walkable to the centre of Ubud. Drivers can be booked from reception easily and reasonably priced, to explore more of Ubud. 

The room itself was absolutely stunning. The high ceilings and layout of the room and garden were jaw dropping. We enjoyed the big bath in the garden and the bath salts and candle provided in the bathroom. The outdoor pool was wonderful and perfect sized for the two of us. We did see a couple of frogs in the evenings, but these were small and harmless. 

The staff went above and beyond to make our trip special. Upon arrival we were greeted with a welcome drink and a smooth check in. After having gone out for dinner we were greeted nicely by all the staff, asking how our dinner was. We especially loved the attention to detail when tidying the room in the evenings. We booked a driver through reception on our final day, and we were pleased to have a driver that was as lovely as the rest of the staff. It was nice that they worked specifically with the hotel and once again we were impressed with the level of service. 

The breakfast was delicious and extensive. We were able to make multiple selections from more western choices and Indonesian choices. 

The bar and the main pool had fantastic views out onto the rice fields. The bar is more peaceful than other places in Ubud, we enjoyed relaxing here in the evening. The drinks were reasonably priced and the staff were lovely. 

We ordered room service a couple of times and the staff that delivered were very attentive. The food ordered was also exceptional. 

Overall, this hotel was a real highlight of our trip. It provided the perfect balance of somewhere to relax and enjoy the amenities, and somewhere allowing you to explore. We loved our time here and will definitely be visiting again!

text:
We have just completed an amazing 4 night stay at Tejaprana Bisma...we loved it! Our room was the 1 bedroom valley view villa and ours was in the furthest corner of the resort with nothing in front or to the side of us but jungle and yes, on occasion...monkeys!

This resort is perfect for you if you are looking for the classic Ubud pool villa experience but without some of the logistical issues of the 5* properties that are often located a 15-25 minute drive out of town. For us, the location is here is perfect...a 5 minute walk to the Monkey Forest Road and the start of so many great restaurant choices within about 20 mins walk.

Back to the resort...it is stunning! The quality of the design & landscaping here has to be seen to be believed! We were mesmerised by the mature tropical plants each time we walked through the resort...it's incredible. The finish both in the communal areas and in the villas is of very high quality.

All staff in the resort are very friendly and well intentioned, albeit I'd say they are quite a junior team and will probably benefit from a bit more experience but I have no doubt they'll get there. As an example, I'd say having a different staff member coming past every 60 seconds asking how your food is is a bit overbearing! The intention is good, the execution is just a bit off.

There is something for everyone on the a la carte breakfast menu...the smoothie bowls are of course a highlight but everything is great! Well, except perhaps the 'hydrolyzed banana'...still not sure what that was about but won't order again!

The villa, outside area and plunge pool are fantastic! The solid stone bath tub, amazing, and the shower cleverly designed to allow access from the inside and outside (with lockable door). We loved the furnishings and copious lighting options...there has been a lot of thought put into it and it shows.

We had monkey experiences on both our first and last mornings...in the latter case it seemed like hundreds of them were making their way into the resort from below and eventually they ended up in our villa garden / on the roof. All good fun and pretty harmless...staff were out gently convincing them to go back to where they came from!

In short, we had an amazing stay, both the resort and Ubud were suberb...would not hesitate to come back!

text:
Review from a Hilton Diamond, IHG platinum sphere, and Bonvoy gold member. Stay in hotels for 125+ nights/year. Highly experienced reviewer of new hotels. 

The below feedback was provided to management during our stay, an apology was received -> but no action taken whatsoever during the remaining three days stay. This tells me that the GM does not take guest feedback serious. 

Let me start of by saying that this hotel is a 13/dozen property. Whilst other hotels that are newly opened, try to stick to formulas that work but always try to create something refreshing and new, Tejaprana doesn’t put any effort into doing something new. Everything has been done and dusted already, and hence it feels like a deja vu experience, whilst missing the complete excitement of staying in a new hotel. 

Second, the staff here needs better training. Bali hospitality is renowned internationally, but here it is just not on par with any 5, 4, even 3 star hotel in Bali. Hence for 200/250 euro per night -> go somewhere else. You’ll be much more satisfied. 

Third, the dinner and breakfast experience is simply said very poor. I don’t know what’s worse, the fact that the food is pathetic, or that the staff just doesn’t give a damn about the feedback. Is this arrogance? Staying in the newly opened Tejaprana Hotel. This must be one of, if not the, worst restaurants in Bali and Indonesia. 

Long waiting times (whilst a lot of staff, and nearly empty restaurant). Live acoustic music very loud, unable to have a conversation. Ordered the Chicken Satay, the national dish, of which one can assume that with an Indonesian chef nothing can go wrong. Guess again... It came stone-cold (despite being served on a mini bbq, which was not lit... what’s the purpose?). Both the serving of mine, and the one of my wife. The chicken was clearly pre-cooked, and microwaved. But apparently too short. 

On the menu it said it came with Pickled vegetables and Chili soy sauce (as it should be). But they “forgot about this”... when asked the staff, they said that they just found it better to be replaced with something else (which was awe full!). For the children we order the penne carbonara. Again, what can go wrong? The pasta was well undercooked, and some pieces raw. 

Then, to make all of the experience even worse, the waitress said it was not happy hour (it was finished), whilst on the menu it was written that it lasted until 21.00. Such an embarrassing argument, we suspect they tried to rip us of, even whilst being in-house guests. Last, when we left we were asked feedback... when we said this was the most horrible dinner we had so far, our feedback was ignored. Then the waitress said the chef would come to talk to us, which never happened. 

Next morning breakfast, was just as sad as dinner. Warm smoothie bowl (how?!), lacking inspiration nasi goring (no condiments, no spice, nothing...., why?). The croissants were actually decent. 

Fourth, it’s clear that the architects have done an outstanding job (also at the other Tejaprana in ubud, it’s a copy almost, though the rooms here are much bigger). But even a great design cannot compensate. 

The pool by the restaurant is really tiny (and since the allow guests from outside it fills up quickly leaving no room for in-house guests. The plunger in the room is indeed very small, but Ok. 

We had water pressure issues throughout our stay. We addressed it, fixed shortly and then came back. After two days finally resolved. 

Check in / front desk staff misses enthusiasm. Stone cold welcome, tried to make a joke but it didn’t really help. Even the rosella welcome drink is boring, and copied from all other hotels in Jalan Bisma (Bisma 8, Goya...) When arrived, two bellboys stood outside looking at how I was offloading our heavy luggage from the car. Come on, a helping hand can’t do any harm right? Probably again due to lack of training. 

Last, something they can’t really help... is there is MASSIVE construction going on. From the pool you are looking and listening at a huge mess on the west side. Noise from early morning till late evening. It just messes up the serenity. The whole of Jalan Bisma is one big construction site. Management should give discounts to justify for staying here until the construction is finished. 

All in all conclusion, if they replace the head chef (and upgrade the menu), stop the live music, train the restaurant and front desk staff, try to do something different, give some discount for the construction, replace the cold lighting in the bathroom, they could earn being a 4 star hotel. Until then, for this price to find something MUCH better in Bali and Ubud.
title: Not worth it, go elsewhere for better value

owner_response.text:
Dear Dinish,

Swastiastu! Greetings from Tejaprana Bisma. 

I regret your stay with us was far from your expectations. Thank you for emailing your feedback a day into your stay and offering “if anything you like me to change.” 

Upon receiving you’re email, our Resort Manager, who is in charge at the property, met you in person to apologise for the inconveniences you experienced and to decline your offer, stating that her, and our, main concern was to correct the shortcomings to your stay, not some rating. Having coordinated the with her team, she received no further complaints from you during the rest of your stay. 

While parts of your review comes down to personal preference and taste, other parts do need to be addressed. 

First and foremost, on behalf our team, I must apologise again if the satay you and your wife ordered took a long time coming, missing the pickles, and was cold by the time you started consuming it. However, I can assure you that the satay was neither cooked nor heated in a microwave. Unfortunately, you were seated right above the speaker for the live music. Not ideal, I admit, but hardly a reason stop having live music altogether. Also, I am sorry for the misunderstanding about happy hour. What the waitress meant to explain was that the particular item you ordered was not included in happy hour. We have no intentions of conning you out of a bottle of beer. 

On the other hand, our pasta is prepared al dente, not undercooked. I am surprised you’ve never come across warm smoothie bowls in your many hotel stays. It is in fact one of our most popular breakfast items. 

The swimming pool by our restaurant is large enough measuring 17.5 m x 8 m. Our records did not show there were outside guest at the time your family came to use it, just other in-house guests who got there earlier. After all, it is a communal pool and we have been running at near full occupancy for a while.

Our security camera footage shows that when you first arrived you and the driver immediately offloaded your luggage and our staff assisted by carrying them to the lobby. 

Again, thank you for your feedback. It is much appreciated and priceless as a case study in our effort to improve and iron out the shortcomings in our services and product offerings. We prefer to do so through training, guidance and correcting, not by firing from the hip. 

Sincerely,
Andra Djajadiningrat

Wir würden jederzeit wieder kommen und sich sehr froh das Hotel gebucht zu haben.

text:
Номера(домики/виллы) производят впечатление. Высокие потолки, красивый дизайн, шикарный вид, чистый бассейн, напор горячей воды просто фантастический. Ничего никуда не вытекает, не подтекает, не капает. Все на высоте. Расположение отеля тоже отличное- рядом куча ресторанчиков, до леса обезьян и «тропы художников» можно дойти пешком. Обезьяны приходят на территорию отеля 2-3 раза в день и ведут себя крайне культурно. Вообще, после тайских и вьетнамских обезьян, их сородичи на Бали произвели крайне положительное впечатление:)
В отеле и поблизости принимают к оплате российские UP:)

Уборка террасы хромает на обе ноги. Обезьяны имеют обыкновение ходить в туалет, соответственно, продукты их жизнедеятельности желательно убирать, а пол мыть. Текстиль неплохо бы выглядел в турецкой трешке, а не в этом замечательном месте. Утром топают обезьяны. Но еще раньше поют птицы. Улица Бисма вроде бы тихая, но дойти до ее конца пешком, то ещё приключение. Рекомендую идти по параллельной улочке (Monkey Forest). Завтрак в отеле так себе. Да и вообще , еда в Убуде не впечатлила от слова никак. Ходили в топовые заведения по Трипадвайсеру- абсолютно ничего выдающегося. Соусов нет, как класса, качество продуктов, приготовления, сервиса на 3+. Pistachio отличался в лучшую сторону наличием музыки. Туда сходили 2 раза.
В общем, отель замечательный, для размещения в Убуде - рекомендую

text:
Très joli hotel ouvert il y'a un an, tout près de la Monkey Forest (5Min à pieds) mais au bout de la très calme Bisma Road.
Jolie piscine à débordement avec vue sur la vallée.
Bon afternoon tea à 16h.
Personnel attentif, meme si nous avons été un peu étonné qu'à notre arrivée à 14h30 il n'y ait qu'une personne à l'accueil, et que notre chambre ne soit pas prete, ce qui pour un établissement de ce standing est un peu surprenant...
Nous avions une chambre vue jardin avec piscine privative. Très jolie chambre, bien équipée.
Nourriture très correcte, notamment le petit déjeuner (à la carte, pas de buffet).
Emplacement bien pour visiter le centre d'Ubud à pied.
Après, pour un prix d'environ 200€ la nuit pour les chambres les moins cheres, je pense qu'il y'a d'autres options tout aussi bonne sur Bisma Road (le Goya, le Bisma Eight ...), voire beaucoup moins cher.

Le Tejaprana Bisma reste néanmoins un très bon hotel et un bon choix !

text: Замечательный, новый, уютный отель.Расположен рядом с Лесом обезьян в Убуде, в конце улицы, которая идет параллельно основной прогулочной. Заселили быстро, персонал приветливый,с первых минут ощущается балийская атмосфера.Виллы просто великолепны.Идеальная чистота.Удобная кровать, выбор подушек, продуманный до мелочей дизайн.Набор мини косметики включает все и даже соль для ванны, которая находится на открытом воздухе. Общий бассейн с красивым видом на рисовые террасы и джунгли. Территория просто утопает в зелени и цветах.Это место единения с природой, полный релакс и романтик.Вкусная еда в основном ресторане, качественный и быстрый румсервис. Очень запомнился сигнатурный коктейль Пандан коллада, самый вкусный аналог Пина коллады на Бали. Из пожеланий, хотелось бы на завтрак добавить гранолу, в сочетании с вашими домашними йогуртами будет прекрасно. Спасибо персоналу отеля за  образцовый сервис и атмосферу, которую вы дарите своим гостям.

text:
Ik weet niet waar ik moet beginnen, werkelijk alles maar dan ook alles was een 10! Wij waren ontzetten verrast door de vriendelijkheid van het personeel of dat bij de receptie was, restaurant, housekeeping, tuinier of masseuse. Iedereen, maar ook iedereen is gericht om je verblijf zo comfortabel mogelijk te maken. 
Wij hebben initieel 1 week geboekt, maar vonden het hotel zo leuk en wouden in Ubud langer blijven, dat wij nog 1 week hebben geboekt. 
Receptie: Wat een leuke ontvangst (wij kwamen om 02:00 aan). Er wordt tijd genomen om je rustig alles uit te leggen, je wordt naar je kamer gebracht. Tijdens je verblijf wordt je bij het verlaten en terugkeren naar het hotel altijd begroet en met oprechte interesse gevraagd wat je gaat doen of hebt gedaan.
Restaurant: Ontbijt is werkelijk uitgebreid en lekker. Twee weken lang verheugden wij ons elke ochtend op het ontbijt. Het is geen lopend buffet, maar a la cart ontbijt. Van smoothie bowls, via pannenkoeken tot verschillende soorten eiergerechten. Ook lunch en diner is op het niveau. Wij hebben maar paar keer gegeten, maar het was erg lekker.

Wunderschönes & sehr im Detailverliebtes Hotel. Wir hatten eine Poolvilla mit Blick auf den Dschungel, einfach traumhaft. Sehr bequemes Bett, großes Badezimmer und die Terrasse ist einfach wunderschön mit toller Sitzmöglichkeit, Badewanne aus Stein, bequeme Liegen und Sonne satt - den ganzen Tag. Die Geräuschkulisse ist toll, am Abend wird der Dschungel erst so richtig wach - hat uns aber nicht gestört. Wenn jemand beim schlafen empfindlich ist empfiehlt sich Ohrobax. 
Am Morgen hatten wir Besuch von einem Affen und hatten vergessen die Tür zu zu machen, dieser hat sich über den Obstteller her gemacht, seit dem war dann unsere Türe immer zu :)
Das Personal ist sehr freundlich, wirklich sehr aufmerksam und immer gut gelaunt.
Da ich leider zu einem Facharzt musste, organisierte mir das Team von Rezeption einen Termin und Transfer. Hier fühlt man sich wirklich gut aufgehoben. Die Lage ist auch gut, nach einem Spaziergang ist man im Zentrum, man kann aber auch den Shuttle ins Zentrum nutzen, dieser fährt glaube alle zwei Stunden. 
Das Frühstück ist sehr gut, für mich fast zu viel, ich bin aber kein Frühstücker und bestelle daher kleinere Portionen. 
Ein wirklich gelungener Aufenthalt, wenn Ubud dann sicherlich wieder das Tejaprana Bisma.
Vielen Dank für die wunderschöne Zeit, wir haben den Aufenthalt sehr genossen.

Wir hatten die Valley View Villa 102 (also mit Tal/Jungle Blick). Zimmer wunderschöner Mix aus Moderne und Bali Style - sehr neu und hochwertig, da das Hotel erst seit Februar eröffnet wurde. 
Die Aussicht ist einfach grandios - nur Jungle und Abends geht die Sonne noch direkt am eigenen Plunge-Pool unter. Morgens hat man das Erlebnis von den Affen, die auf dem Weg sind zum Monkey Forest, geweckt zu werden. Sie laufen direkt in Front des Plunge-Pools oder über die Dächer. Ein einzigartiges Erlebnis so nah an wilden Affen zu sein - doch Vorsicht man sollte diese Tiere respektieren, nicht unterschätzen und auch nicht unbedingt was draußen liegen lassen.
Die Anlage fließt super in die übrige Natur ein. 
Das Restaurant ist offen gestaltet - der Küchenchef versteht sein Handwerk - wirklich ausgezeichnetes Essen. Preis-Leistung ist fair. Man merkt das auf frisches Essen wert gelegt wird. 
Der Spa ist sehr gut und hat ein tolles Ambiente. 
Das Hotel hat eine gut Ausgangsposition, man ist in 5 Minuten auf der Jalan Monkey Forest (Einkaufsstraße von Ubud), dort findet man einen kleinen Supermarkt, Eingang zum Monkey Forest, Souvenirshops und Restaurants. 
Der Coco Supermarkt ( großer Supermarkt) ist gut erreichbar. 

Das ganze Team vom Hotel ist super. Ein junges, offenes, super freundlich und zuvorkommendes Team. Man merkt das die Mitarbeiter/innen gut geschult sind. 

Mein Mann hat schon am zweiten Tag sich den Fuß umgeschlagen und einen Bänderriss erlitten, man hat uns Eis zum kühlen gegeben, Verbandsmaterial zum Stützen und es wurde gefragt ob man ihn zur Klinik fahren soll. Es wurde sich immer erkundigt wie es ihm geht. So eine Aufmerksamkeit haben wir in einem Hotel noch nie erlebt. 

Wir würden wiederkommen. 

Dieses Hotel ist eine absolute Empfehlung. 

Eine nicht zu große Anlage. Man kann komplett Entspannen. Privatsphäre in der Villa. 
Tolles Ambiente und es wird jeder Wunsch dort erfüllt.
